      "text": "All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.08,
      "end": 11.2,
      "text": "For more information, or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.82,
      "end": 15.8,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.44,
      "end": 21.04,
      "text": "A Subspables, the Eagle, and the Cox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.2,
      "end": 27.64,
      "text": "There were two Coxs in the same farm yard, and they fought to decide who should be master.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 28.56,
      "end": 33.64,
      "text": "When the fight was over, the beaten one went and hit himself in a dark corner,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.32,
      "end": 39.06,
      "text": "while the victor flew up onto the roof of the stables and crowed lustly.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 39.62,
      "end": 45.92,
      "text": "But an eagle espied him from high up in the sky, and swooped down and carried him off.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 46.88,
      "end": 52.02,
      "text": "Fourth with, the other cock came out of his corner and ruled the roost without a rival.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 53.62,
      "end": 55.9,
      "text": "Pride comes before a fall.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 55.9,
      "end": 60.38,
      "text": "End of the Eagle and the Cox.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
